cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper is about text classification using a weighted recurrent neural network. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with information retrieval and semantic analysis, which could place it in cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the use of neural networks suggests that it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
